><i> zero</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> decrease in damage done, since my AC never changed between the time I logged using CS2, and minutes later with CS3.<br><br>Even on a greencon mob (Bloodmaw), with the exact same AC, the damage I took decreased significantly by simply going from CS2, to CS3.<br><br>Essentially, it'll work similarly if you have 1000 AC, or if you have 1500 AC. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uhaass.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haass</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 176<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/10/02 1:45:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1648.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Combat Stability/AC Cap</span><hr size=1> Ya, there's no way it raises your ac cap.<br><br>I'm under the AC cap, just hit 1230 something unbuffed recently, and CS is a very noticable difference.<br><br>If it raised the AC cap, I wouldn't notice it, and I do. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udracillionofqeynos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DracillionofQeynos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 202<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/10/02 7:31:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1648.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Combat Stability/AC Cap</span><hr size=1> I'm kind of in the same boat as you guys as I don't see how CS could raise the AC cap.  I've heard the 1320 number thrown around with CS3.  Can anyone explain this? <p><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=127089">Dracillion of Qeynos</a><BR>Warlord of Omani<BR>Bertoxxulous Server</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utuggbarg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TuggbarG</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/10/02 1:27:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1648.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://canflag.ptbcanadian.com/images/animated/provii/cf2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Combat Stability/AC Cap</span><hr size=1> Think of this as a permanent 'defence discipline' that is activated all the time.  It simply increases your damage avoidance. <p><CENTER><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=59492" target="_blank">Tuggbar's Stash</a></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uvaraho1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Varaho1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 227<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/10/02 1:52:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1648.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Combat Stability/AC Cap</span><hr size=1> Post to logs no longer there <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Did you still get hit for max damage or no?<br><br>If yes then calling it mini defensive wouldn't be right. It would be more along the lines of  +% to your rolls so you avoid part of the damage more often, or avoid more damage at the same rate.<br><br>Perhaps the same thing with avoidance?<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> EDIT:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Bah fixed the Emotcon <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=170513">Varaho Carnicero</a><BR> 55th Human Myrmidon of the Eternal Bloodguard <BR>Xegony</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uvaraho1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Varaho1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0> at: 6/10/02 1:56:58 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utenakha.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tenakha</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/con's RED</span><br>  Posts: 351<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/10/02 2:06:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1648.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Combat Stability/AC Cap</span><hr size=1> It does not function like defensive, defensive reduces every hit you take, just log dmg taken from a mob with and without defensive and you'll see.   <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7197 style="text-decoration: none">Gorlab</a> 60 Warlord<BR>Tenakha 53 Druid<BR>Officer of <a href=http://www.keepersofthefaith.org style="text-decoration: none">Keepers Of The Faith</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ushelrabbi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shelrabbi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 140<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/10/02 3:13:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1648.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Combat Stability/AC Cap</span><hr size=1> I love these conversations. Especially since all the info is already on this board. Possibly not in the FAQ though, so here's the jist.<br><br>The softcap is whatever the softcap is. Completely and totally irrelevant for the purposes of this discussion.<br><br>AC is made up of 3 components (I think). 2 of them are Damage avoidance and Damage mitigation. DA is your ability to dodge/parry/riposte/block (monk) etc. DM is your ability to take less damage then you were hit for. IE you get hit for 1400, but it only says on your screen you got hit for 500, and only 500 is subtracted from your current hp total.<br><br>Now, in the last conversation we had about this, someone brought up that it was specifically said by a verant employee at the last fan faire that there is a softcap, but that that cap only applies to one of the 3 components of AC. <br><br>I'm pretty sure it's the DA component, but no one actually knows since he never said and the rest of what we know about AC is from parsing and comparing against theories.<br><br>So, if the DA component is the capped one, then Combat Stability probably only effects the DM, which means that at any AC, over the softcap or not, you will get hit for noticeably less damage then you would without combat stability.<br><br>Any questions? <p>Shelrabbi Hassida<BR>Tallon Zek<BR>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=216910<BR><br>"Beer is the path to the dark side. Beer leads to drunkeness. Drunkeness leads to beer goggles. Beer goggles lead to dirty womanOnce you get a dirty woman on your jock, forever will she dominate your destiny. Besides, Whiskey is the drink of the true jedi." -Yoda</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=